bug.short_desc: controls disappear when using search without repository

long_desc.thetext:
Open Search dialog, click Task Search tab but have no repository(?) set. Get an info dialog indicating need a repository. When info dialog is closed the Task Search tab is missing its UI Click the File Search tab and it also is missing most of its UI (the Scope block and its controls are still visible)
Closing and re-opening Search restores the UI
Thanks Chris

Can you reproduce this behaviour if you do not use the 'Task Search' tab? I believe that's from Mylyn. So it would be helpful if we could remove as many variables as possible.
Some screenshots would also be helpful.

Disabling the tab via Customize (or just not clicking the Task Search tab) avoids the problem. It doesn't seem to break the program, just doesn't redraw the controls.
I just set up a repository (connected to Eclipse's Bugzilla) and the search works as expected. So the key seems to be not having a repository set up in Mylyn
I'm having technical difficulties that prevent me from grabbing a screen shot, but will attach some as soon as I work them out

Do you see anything in your workspace's logs? Check your <workspace>/.metadata/.log file. I recommend renaming it to something else and then trying to reproduce the problem so that you have a clean log file.
Alternatively, you should also try to reproduce the problem on a completely fresh/non-existent workspace to further reduce the number of variables with this problem.

I have not been able to reproduce the problem. The info dialog is displayed and the search dialog continues to work after it is closed.
Chris, which version of Eclipse and Mylyn are you using?
As a work around you could try to create a repository in the Task Repositories view, e.g. a Bugzilla repository for Eclipse.org.
